text: Hey @UPSHelp my package shows delivered but it’s not here. You deliver packages from this same shipper multiple times a week and today my package is nowhere to be found. I was home all day and my dog hates delivery men. What gives?

So I still don’t have my package that was supposedly delivered but was definitely not.. and the local team that was promised to call me within an hour twice last week never called.. @UPS you’re no bueno with me right now. #justfindmypackage #overit

@shoewhoreninja The investigation is still open on the package and UPS is currently looking for the shipment. You will need to keep in contact with the shipper as any claim details will be sent directly to them. So you know an investigation can take up to eight business days. ^ML https://t.co/wKJHDXWGRQ
@UPSHelp Yes, I contacted the shipper, my employer. I’ll wait the 8 days.. it’s about like waiting for the phone calls that never came.
@UPSHelp so it’s been 8 days or more.. what now?
@shoewhoreninja We have sent notification to your shipper. Please remain in touch with the sender for any further updates or resolution. ^SK

@UPSHelp Yeah, as of yesterday they had still not been contacted by UPS. I work for the shipper so I have constant contact with them. Maybe try harder, ups... I feel like you’ve just washed your hands of this. #disappointed

@shoewhoreninja I apologize that you feel that way. We don't receive notification on our end of the results. That is sent by our investigation team directly to the shipper recorded on the investigation. I suggest having them contact us directly if they have not been notified. ^ZM
